beer.beer_description:
SMaSH Mosaic IPA with Hemp.

This beer is brewed in honor and memoriam of a man we knew as Bombay.
Originally from India he ended up in Uganda during Idi Amin’s reign of terror.
Thankfully he managed to escape and made his way to Christiania, where he found peace and a place where he belonged.
Bombay would often ask for a Ganesh beer, but back then he had to drink a macro brew instead of this locally brewed IPA.
And with its slightly bitter taste, fruity nose, a little hemp and 6.4% alcohol we are 100% certain he would have enjoyed it.
So here’s to you Bombay, cheers.
